05:19.928 --> 05:22.974
to make it look
like it was written back then,

05:22.974 --> 05:25.455
contemporaneously.

05:25.455 --> 05:27.414
- Oh. Mm.
- Oh, uh-huh?

05:27.414 --> 05:28.632
- Got it.
- Mm-hmm.

05:28.632 --> 05:30.417
You want me
to alter the metadata

05:30.417 --> 05:31.809
to help you commit fraud.

05:31.809 --> 05:34.421
This has been fun, Chloe.
You're fun.

05:34.421 --> 05:36.640
You can go now.

05:36.640 --> 05:38.033
Sadie,
did Katherine Hastings know

05:38.033 --> 05:40.252
the cars contained
defective locking pawls?

05:40.252 --> 05:42.994
Well, Nate, that assumes
that the pawls were defective,

05:42.994 --> 05:44.431
which we're not saying.

05:44.431 --> 05:46.128
It also implies
that the Hydra's a car,

05:46.128 --> 05:49.044
when, actually
it's a light SUV, so...

05:49.044 --> 05:50.132
Andrea.

05:50.132 --> 05:51.394
Uh, yes, there are currently

05:51.394 --> 05:53.483
more than one million Hydras
on the road.

05:53.483 --> 05:54.832
Oof, according to you.

05:54.832 --> 05:57.008
No, according
to your website.

05:57.008 --> 05:58.619
Well, I don't make
the website.

05:58.619 --> 06:00.403
