10:04.734 --> 10:06.431
They want to set
an emergency meeting.

10:06.431 --> 10:08.085
- Soren?
- Chairman of the Board.

10:08.085 --> 10:09.478
They were already after my job.

10:09.478 --> 10:11.741
I doubt they're calling
to tell me that a scandal

10:11.741 --> 10:14.483
and a plummeting stock price
have made them reconsider.

10:14.483 --> 10:16.311
Look, my advice is,
push them off.

10:16.311 --> 10:18.618
Even if they are thinking
about replacing you,

10:18.618 --> 10:21.664
when you fix this crisis,
you'll show what you're worth.

10:21.664 --> 10:24.406
It's true. Every disaster
presents an opportunity.

10:24.406 --> 10:26.277
This fire
could be my Chernobyl.

10:26.277 --> 10:28.453
Uh, that one didn't go well,
though, right?

10:28.453 --> 10:29.846
- Yeah, but it could've.
- But it didn't.

10:29.846 --> 10:31.021
Yeah, but it will.

10:31.021 --> 10:33.110
Okay. All right.
Positive Chernobyl.

10:33.110 --> 10:35.243
Chernobyl.

10:35.243 --> 10:37.462
I keep refreshing
my news feed,

10:37.462 --> 10:39.290
waiting for them
to get this fire out.

10:39.290 --> 10:40.770
It's awful.

10:40.770 --> 10:42.772
Look, whatever happens,
you're gonna be taken care of.

10:42.772 --> 10:43.947
You're like family.

10:43.947 --> 10:46.471
Worst comes to worst,
come work for me.

10:46.471 --> 10:48.299
Work for you?
Doing what?

10:48.299 --> 10:49.649
I don't know.
You could be my...

10:49.649 --> 10:51.476
style guy/personal assistant.

10:51.476 --> 10:53.957
It'd be like "Entourage,"
where I'm the "star"

10:53.957 --> 10:56.133
and you're my best friend
who also works for me.

10:56.133 --> 10:57.439
We could be
double-teaming girls

10:57.439 --> 10:58.875
in my hot tub every night.

10:58.875 --> 11:00.485
Yeah, I don't remember
that happening on "Entourage."

11:00.485 --> 11:02.705
It did, offscreen.
But how awesome would that be?

11:02.705 --> 11:04.664
You'd be my Turtle.
- Yeah.

11:04.664 --> 11:06.491
Yeah, thanks.
I'll think about it.

11:06.491 --> 11:08.058
Would you rather be E?

11:08.058 --> 11:10.713
I just figured Turtle's
the closest one to a Black guy.

11:10.713 --> 11:12.367
Mm.

11:12.367 --> 11:13.890
- Sadie. Miss Ryan.
- Sadie, are you concerned

11:13.890 --> 11:15.936
that Payne will lose customers
over this?

11:15.936 --> 11:18.503
Uh, well, let's see, you've
lost most of your readers,

11:18.503 --> 11:20.070
and you're still in business.

11:20.070 --> 11:21.463
Tom.

11:21.463 --> 11:23.073
Do you accept responsibility
for the fire?

11:23.073 --> 11:27.121
Do you accept responsibility
for your weak chin?

11:27.121 --> 11:29.427
Wow, attacking a reporter's
physical appearance--

11:29.427 --> 11:30.690
not what I would've done.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.169
I mean, I told her
to be aggressive,

11:32.169 --> 11:33.693
but this is just catty.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.956
You know, and you're gonna
feel like an idiot, Tom,

11:35.956 --> 11:37.348
like an absolute moron

11:37.348 --> 11:39.089
because you and your
Chicken Little friends here,

11:39.089 --> 11:40.525
you're bitching and whining,

11:40.525 --> 11:42.527
when I guarantee that this fire

11:42.527 --> 11:45.835
will be out in two days, so f--

11:45.835 --> 11:47.054
That was one week ago,

11:47.054 --> 11:48.925
but the Payne Fire
continues to rage on,

11:48.925 --> 11:51.362
<i>now covering
over 100,000 acres</i>

11:51.362 --> 11:53.451
<i>and zero percent contained.</i>

11:55.149 --> 11:56.933
Smoke and ash
from the inferno is drifting

11:56.933 --> 11:57.934
across the country,

11:57.934 --> 11:59.675
reddening the skies over Payne,

11:59.675 --> 12:01.111
as we continue wondering,

12:01.111 --> 12:03.548
what did they know,
and when did they know it?

12:03.548 --> 12:06.116
Welp, who would've thought
the weather geeks had

12:06.116 --> 12:08.858
no [bleep] damn clue
what they were talking about?

12:11.078 --> 12:13.602
But, you know, there's always
black swan events

12:13.602 --> 12:15.604
that you can't predict, right?
- Uh, more bad news:

12:15.604 --> 12:18.041
my PI couldn't dig up any dirt
on that family.

12:18.041 --> 12:19.869
Apparently they were his kids,

12:19.869 --> 12:21.871
and no one
was molesting anyone.

12:21.871 --> 12:23.612
Gosh, you really
cannot win them all.

12:23.612 --> 12:26.223
Also, our share price
stumbled another 12%,

12:26.223 --> 12:29.357
and Biden called us "a blight
on our national honor."

12:29.357 --> 12:31.751
Wow.
Little harsh there, Joe, right?

12:31.751 --> 12:33.796
All right,
onward and upward, right?

12:33.796 --> 12:35.885
Thanks, guys.
- Okay, yeah, back at it.

12:35.885 --> 12:37.757
Yeah.

12:39.106 --> 12:40.803
How are you doing
with all this?

12:40.803 --> 12:42.413
I know you're dealing
with a lot.

12:42.413 --> 12:43.588
- Me?
- Yeah.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.416
Yeah, I'm fine.
Don't worry about me.

12:45.416 --> 12:47.201
If you ever want to talk
about it,

12:47.201 --> 12:48.637
you know,
just as, like, friends...

12:48.637 --> 12:50.117
I know we're not
friends, technically.

12:50.117 --> 12:52.206
I don't want to overstep,
but we could be more--

12:52.206 --> 12:53.816
Don't have to put
a label on it.

12:53.816 --> 12:55.470
Look what came
for the conference room.

12:55.470 --> 12:57.646
Oh, see, things
are looking up already.

12:57.646 --> 13:00.910
I still see wah-room.

13:00.910 --> 13:02.782
<i>Uh, hey, guys?</i>

13:02.782 --> 13:04.784
Uh, some of our internal emails

13:04.784 --> 13:07.134
have been leaking to the press,
and it really sounds

13:07.134 --> 13:08.831
like we're running around
with our hair on fire.

13:08.831 --> 13:10.267
It's embarrassing.

13:10.267 --> 13:12.443
So maybe please stop using
the terms like, uh,

13:12.443 --> 13:15.272
"disaster," "clunker,"
"dumpster fire,"

13:15.272 --> 13:18.362
"bloodbath," "death wagon,"
"Satan's wet dream,"

13:18.362 --> 13:20.103
and, of course, "[bleep] show,"
"[bleep] sandwich,"

13:20.103 --> 13:22.105
"[bleep]storm,"
and "[bleep] fire."

13:22.105 --> 13:24.412
Uh, what's a [bleep] fire?

13:24.412 --> 13:26.762
I can only assume it's a fire
made of [bleep]--I don't know.

13:26.762 --> 13:27.937
Checks out.

13:27.937 --> 13:29.852
<i>I am not a bad person.</i>

13:29.852 --> 13:31.245
I don't want things to burn.

13:31.245 --> 13:32.899
Is that what you guys think,

13:32.899 --> 13:34.857
that, like,
I'm on the fire's side,

13:34.857 --> 13:37.555
that I'm some mean fire lady?

13:37.555 --> 13:40.036
This is hard.

13:40.036 --> 13:43.518
Do you know how hard this
has been for-- like, for me?

13:43.518 --> 13:46.651
And not that--
It's not about me. I...

13:46.651 --> 13:48.958
I'm just--next question.

13:48.958 --> 13:50.786
<i>Oh, God.</i>

13:50.786 --> 13:52.570
Thank you. You have no idea
how good that feels.

13:52.570 --> 13:54.790
That is making me
physically ill.

13:54.790 --> 13:56.836
Oh, right, yes, it's
my dermatological condition

13:56.836 --> 13:58.446
that's making you feel sick and
not the fact that you're eating

13:58.446 --> 13:59.839
cake topped with butter.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.188
It's not cake.
It's a muffin.

14:01.188 --> 14:02.450
A chocolate muffin is cake.

14:02.450 --> 14:04.191
It just has a little jacket
around it.

14:04.191 --> 14:06.149
How the hell
does she remain so calm?

14:06.149 --> 14:07.542
She the one
with the job in jeopardy.

14:07.542 --> 14:09.326
Meanwhile,
we the ones falling apart.

14:09.326 --> 14:11.502
<i>- Okay...</i>
- Nothing gets to her.

14:11.502 --> 14:13.200
You look
like you're doing okay.

14:13.200 --> 14:15.942
I'm not. I haven't pooped
once since all this started.

14:15.942 --> 14:17.900
It's been over a month.

14:17.900 --> 14:19.902
I don't know where it goes.

14:19.902 --> 14:23.210
I guess it just, like...
evaporates or something.

14:23.210 --> 14:25.212
<i>What day is it?</i>

14:25.212 --> 14:26.909
- Wednesday.
- Yeah.

14:26.909 --> 14:28.693
No.

14:28.693 --> 14:30.608
Friday?
- Mm.

14:30.608 --> 14:33.350
I can't do
any more press conferences.

14:33.350 --> 14:35.918
I feel like I'm in one
of those movies

14:35.918 --> 14:38.225
where you replay the same day
on a loop,

14:38.225 --> 14:40.053
but somehow
I'm learning less each time.

14:40.053 --> 14:42.142
It's been pretty rough.

14:42.142 --> 14:44.231
Don't laugh.
It's...

14:44.231 --> 14:47.364
You try embarrassing yourself
on national TV.

14:47.364 --> 14:50.715
Uh, you mean like that time
I was on a news program

14:50.715 --> 14:53.370
and I talked about
how into a coworker I was?

14:53.370 --> 14:56.069
To which she replied...

14:56.069 --> 14:58.071
- That's not what I did.
- Uh, it's pretty close.

14:58.071 --> 14:59.289
- That's not what I did.
- It's pretty close.

14:59.289 --> 15:01.030
You know my friends
still make fun of me

15:01.030 --> 15:02.249
for getting denied
in prime time?

15:02.249 --> 15:05.121
- I wasn't denying you.
- I'm joking.

15:05.121 --> 15:07.210
No, but I'm just saying,
it wasn't, like, personal.

15:07.210 --> 15:08.603
- Hmm.
- You know, if we didn't work

15:08.603 --> 15:11.388
15 feet from each other,
then who knows?

15:11.388 --> 15:13.390
So, if Payne
goes out of business

15:13.390 --> 15:15.218
and we all go to prison, then...

15:15.218 --> 15:17.220
Just give me a call
when you get out.

15:17.220 --> 15:19.179
That's something
to look forward to.

15:19.179 --> 15:21.398
Night.
- Night.

15:25.054 --> 15:27.361
<i>Hundreds of exhausted firefighters</i>

15:27.361 --> 15:29.754
<i>are working into the night
battling the Payne Fire,</i>

15:29.754 --> 15:31.104
<i>which is now the largest
in the history of the state.</i>

15:31.104 --> 15:32.366
Wait. Stop.
Is--is that us?

15:32.366 --> 15:34.237
No, that's some fat guy.

15:34.237 --> 15:36.413
<i>... have been forced
to abandon their homes.</i>

15:36.413 --> 15:39.068
Oh, my God, I'm the fat guy.

15:39.068 --> 15:40.940
Okay, guys,
let's stay on task.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.245
Sadie...
- Mm.

15:42.245 --> 15:43.420
How close are they
to putting out the fires?

15:43.420 --> 15:45.205
Last I heard,
they're 2% contained,

15:45.205 --> 15:49.861
but, you know, 2%
of 300,000 acres--that's a lot.

15:49.861 --> 15:51.211
Yes, I like that optimism.

15:51.211 --> 15:53.953
Okay, where are we
with regulatory, Elephant Man?

15:53.953 --> 15:56.303
Uh, yeah, um,
fat stack of fines

15:56.303 --> 15:58.174
and a congressional
investigation, I think.

15:58.174 --> 15:59.915
Our stock's already
at an all-time low.

15:59.915 --> 16:01.351
I had to sell my boat.

16:01.351 --> 16:03.049
Now I'm a guy
with just one boat,

16:03.049 --> 16:04.441
like a frickin' cuck.

16:04.441 --> 16:06.487
How about the recall,
Professor Klump?

16:06.487 --> 16:09.533
Yeah, um, the recall is going
slower than expected,

16:09.533 --> 16:12.406
and, also, it's more expensive
than we expected.

16:12.406 --> 16:13.973
- Oh, my God.
- Oh.

16:13.973 --> 16:16.236
Guys, come on,
it's not that bad, right?

16:16.236 --> 16:17.454
I mean, Ian,
I'm sure you've dealt

16:17.454 --> 16:18.934
with way worse situations
than this.

16:18.934 --> 16:21.023
Uh, no.

16:21.023 --> 16:22.329
Mm.

16:24.070 --> 16:25.680
Okay, well, uh,

16:25.680 --> 16:27.508
I guess tomorrow morning,
we will reconvene.

16:27.508 --> 16:29.292
Uh, you got a meeting
with Soren in the morning.

16:29.292 --> 16:31.642
I couldn't put him off anymore.
He's coming in person.

16:31.642 --> 16:32.992
Ah.

16:32.992 --> 16:35.255
Wow, he's, uh, flying in
for the meeting.

16:35.255 --> 16:36.604
Oh.

16:36.604 --> 16:38.171
Must be important.

16:38.171 --> 16:39.999
Well, he probably doesn't
want to fire you over Zoom.

16:41.391 --> 16:43.524
Okay, like I'm the only one
in here thinking it.

16:43.524 --> 16:45.569
Maybe--maybe he just wants
to see the frogs.

16:45.569 --> 16:47.484
- What frogs?
- You haven't been outside?

16:47.484 --> 16:49.095
There's all these frogs
from the Detroit River

16:49.095 --> 16:50.313
trying to get away
from the smoke.

16:50.313 --> 16:51.706
Yeah, they're everywhere.

16:51.706 --> 16:53.969
They got into my kitchen,
just ribbiting all night.

16:59.366 --> 17:01.585
Wait.
I'm sorry, did you say "frogs"?

17:01.585 --> 17:03.631
- What--what's so funny?
- I mean, it's funny.

17:05.937 --> 17:07.287
These frogs?

17:07.287 --> 17:08.505
Every time, I think to myself,

17:08.505 --> 17:10.333
"This is as bad
as it can get," right?

17:10.333 --> 17:12.553
And then, nope, frogs.

17:15.338 --> 17:17.384
It's biblical, you know?

17:18.950 --> 17:21.953
I mean, there's fires,
darkness, a guy with boils.

17:21.953 --> 17:23.868
T-they're hives.

17:23.868 --> 17:25.348
And now frogs!

17:25.348 --> 17:27.263
Ooh, and my boat--that
could be, like, a Noah thing.

17:27.263 --> 17:30.614
It's--it's gonna be okay.

17:30.614 --> 17:32.399
No, no, no,
it's not gonna be okay, okay?

17:32.399 --> 17:35.358
We all know
it's not gonna be okay.

17:35.358 --> 17:37.230
I mean, I tell you guys
it's gonna be okay.

17:37.230 --> 17:39.971
And you know why?
- 'C--'cause you don't lose?

17:39.971 --> 17:41.538
No, I tell you
it's gonna be okay

17:41.538 --> 17:44.193
so that you all
don't panic, okay?

17:44.193 --> 17:46.543
I mean, outside,
I'm all like,

17:46.543 --> 17:49.111
"Hey, guys, everything's
gonna be just fine.

17:49.111 --> 17:51.113
Brighter days tomorrow.
Cheer up, okay?"

17:51.113 --> 17:52.723
Do you want to know
what I'm thinking inside?

17:52.723 --> 17:55.552
Would you like to know
what I am thinking inside?

17:55.552 --> 17:56.597
Yeah, yeah.

17:56.597 --> 17:58.120
!

17:58.120 --> 18:01.384
We're [bleep]!

18:01.384 --> 18:04.996
We're all [bleep]!

18:04.996 --> 18:07.521
All of us are [bleep]!

18:07.521 --> 18:09.305
All right!

18:09.305 --> 18:11.438
Well, I'd say
I'd see you tomorrow,

18:11.438 --> 18:13.135
but my money's on an asteroid
destroying the planet

18:13.135 --> 18:14.180
by morning.

18:20.011 --> 18:24.146
You're a nation of inbreds!
That's why you lost the war!

18:32.459 --> 18:33.982
Hey.

18:33.982 --> 18:36.115
You meet with Soren yet?
- Not yet.

18:36.115 --> 18:38.900
But I got the heads-up
this morning: I'm out.

18:38.900 --> 18:41.250
- Oh, I'm so sorry.
- Please don't be.

18:41.250 --> 18:42.599
It is fine.

18:42.599 --> 18:43.992
I mean, my lawyer says

18:43.992 --> 18:45.515
that my early-termination
penalties are so broad,

18:45.515 --> 18:47.169
they're gonna end up paying me
more than I would've made

18:47.169 --> 18:48.736
in five years
of actually working here, so...

18:48.736 --> 18:50.172
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

18:50.172 --> 18:52.043
Jeez, I got to check
my contract.

18:52.043 --> 18:55.830
Yeah, I think I am due
for some well-earned self-care.

18:55.830 --> 18:57.962
Spend some time with Richard...
- Yeah.

18:57.962 --> 18:59.834
You know, read, travel,

18:59.834 --> 19:02.489
drink Bellinis on the beach
at dawn.

19:02.489 --> 19:04.143
I'm happy for you.

19:05.883 --> 19:07.146
- Thank you.
- Oh.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.625
Thank you for everything.

19:08.625 --> 19:10.758
- You're welcome.
- Yeah.

19:12.499 --> 19:13.935
And you're welcome, too.

19:13.935 --> 19:15.502
Yes, right,
thank you for everything.

19:15.502 --> 19:16.851
Absolutely are welcome.

19:16.851 --> 19:18.026
Was it one of those little,

19:18.026 --> 19:19.897
polite "thanks, sweetie"
type hugs?

19:19.897 --> 19:22.639
No, it was like
an actual, genuine embrace.

19:22.639 --> 19:23.858
How did she feel?

19:23.858 --> 19:25.033
I feel like she'd feel cold,

19:25.033 --> 19:26.687
like hugging Elsa
from "Frozen."

19:26.687 --> 19:28.123
No, just normal.

19:28.123 --> 19:30.865
She was happy. I think this
is a good thing for her.

19:30.865 --> 19:33.128
Oh, it's the end of an era,
you know?

19:33.128 --> 19:35.609
Not a very long one, but, uh--
but an era nonetheless.

19:35.609 --> 19:37.785
- Yo.
- Mm?

19:37.785 --> 19:39.221
I just had
a telehealth visit,

19:39.221 --> 19:41.789
and doctor said
if I don't poop soon,

19:41.789 --> 19:45.184
they're gonna have to medically
induce the poop out of me.

19:48.317 --> 19:52.539
We, uh, added a little bonus
for bowing out graciously.

19:52.539 --> 19:54.236
It's more than generous.

19:54.236 --> 19:56.369
Well, I'm sorry
about all this.

19:56.369 --> 19:59.198
There's just a lot
of very angry shareholders,

19:59.198 --> 20:01.983
so a few heads have to roll.

20:01.983 --> 20:03.332
A few heads?

20:03.332 --> 20:04.768
I knew about my head.

20:04.768 --> 20:06.988
I didn't realize
that there would be other...

20:06.988 --> 20:09.512
Any specific heads
or just any old head?

20:09.512 --> 20:12.646
Not many, just, you know,
whoever knew about the pawls.

20:12.646 --> 20:14.909
Yeah, um, Cyrus Knight,

20:14.909 --> 20:17.085
Elliot Chisholm, Sadie Ryan,

20:17.085 --> 20:18.913
a few others.
- Okay.

20:18.913 --> 20:20.567
Anyway,
thanks for everything,

20:20.567 --> 20:22.264
and we wish you luck.

20:26.616 --> 20:28.923
Give us six months.

20:28.923 --> 20:30.577
- I'm sorry?
- Yeah, six months.

20:30.577 --> 20:31.795
Let me keep my team.

20:31.795 --> 20:33.144
If--if we can't get
the stock price

20:33.144 --> 20:35.059
back to where it was
before all this happened,

20:35.059 --> 20:38.367
then I will walk, and you
don't have to pay me a dime.

20:38.367 --> 20:39.716
Hang on.

20:39.716 --> 20:41.109
Best-case scenario--

20:41.109 --> 20:43.329
you work your ass off
to make less

20:43.329 --> 20:45.461
than what you already have
on the table in front of you,

20:45.461 --> 20:47.376
or you lose everything.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.641
Oh. Hey.

20:51.641 --> 20:54.035
- Hey.
- Hey, there she is.

20:54.035 --> 20:55.819
- Come here, you.
- No.

20:55.819 --> 20:58.126
- Oh.
- I'm gonna be sticking around.

20:58.126 --> 20:59.780
- Hey.
- I sweet-talked them.

20:59.780 --> 21:01.172
- Wow!
- That's great.

21:01.172 --> 21:03.218
What happened to self-care?

21:03.218 --> 21:06.482
Let's just say I cared more
about something else.

21:06.482 --> 21:08.397
- Huh.
- Hmm.

21:08.397 --> 21:11.008
Basically, they were gonna
fire all you guys,

21:11.008 --> 21:12.706
and I threw myself on a grenade
to save your jobs.

21:12.706 --> 21:16.275
It was very heroic, and you all
owe me big-time, so...

21:16.275 --> 21:17.885
Uh...

21:17.885 --> 21:19.278
Huh.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.410
I am not gonna forget it.
